-- U.S. Public Ridership Rose in the Second Quarter
-- B y   A l e x   T a n z i
-- 2013-09-23T12:00:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-23/u-s-public-ridership-rose-in-the-second-quarter-table-.html
Trips on public transportation  
in the U.S. rose in the second quarter from the same period
last year, according to the American Public Transportation
Association.     Americans taking public transportation rose to 2.7 billion
trips from the same quarter last year. Travel on light rail 
rose to 130 million in the second quarter.  SOURCE: American Public Transportation Association 